Basic Gravity Model vs.Â Land Use Model

Jonathan Kent

sun <- read_rds("~/GoogleDrive/PhD/Paper Three/mob_all.rds") %>% filter(codigo_destino != codigo_residencia & dia == "Sunday") %>% filter(data < as.Date("2021-10-20"))
wed <- read_rds("~/GoogleDrive/PhD/Paper Three/mob_all.rds") %>% filter(codigo_destino != codigo_residencia & dia == "Wednesday") %>% filter(data < as.Date("2021-10-20"))

Part 1: Basic Gravity Models

Basic Gravity Model 1 - Population

s1 <- lm(log(flujo) ~ scale(pob_destino) + scale(pob_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig, data = sun)
w1 <- lm(log(flujo) ~ scale(pob_destino) + scale(pob_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig, data = wed)

Basic Gravity Model 2 - Density

s2 <- lm(log(flujo) ~ scale(dens_destino) + scale(dens_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig, data = sun)
w2 <- lm(log(flujo) ~ scale(dens_destino) + scale(dens_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig, data = wed)

Basic Gravity Model 3 - Population & Area

s3 <- lm(log(flujo) ~ scale(pob_destino) + scale(pob_residencia) + scale(area_destino) + scale(area_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig, data = sun)
w3 <- lm(log(flujo) ~ scale(pob_destino) + scale(pob_residencia) + scale(area_destino) + scale(area_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig, data = wed)

Basic Gravity Model 4 - Density & Area

s4 <- lm(log(flujo) ~ scale(dens_destino) + scale(dens_residencia) + scale(area_destino) + scale(area_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig, data = sun)
w4 <- lm(log(flujo) ~ scale(dens_destino) + scale(dens_residencia) + scale(area_destino) + scale(area_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig, data = wed)

Part 2: Can land cover and/or weather data improve on the best basic model?

Land Cover Model 1 - Urban Fabric Continuity Only

s1_lc <- lm(log(flujo) ~ scale(pob_destino) + scale(pob_residencia) + scale(area_destino) + scale(area_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig + scale(uf_cont_destino) + scale(uf_cont_residencia), data = sun)
w1_lc <- lm(log(flujo) ~ scale(pob_destino) + scale(pob_residencia) + scale(area_destino) + scale(area_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig + scale(uf_cont_destino) + scale(uf_cont_residencia), data = wed)

Land Cover Model 2 - All Land Cover Vars

lc2_formula <- as.formula(paste0("log(flujo) ~ scale(pob_destino) + scale(pob_residencia) + scale(area_destino) + scale(area_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig + ", paste0("scale(",names(sun)[12:23],")", collapse = " + ")))

s2_lc <- lm(formula = lc2_formula, data = sun)
w2_lc <- lm(formula = lc2_formula, data = wed)
s3_wea <- lm(log(flujo) ~ scale(pob_destino) + scale(pob_residencia) + scale(area_destino) + scale(area_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig + temp_residencia + I(temp_residencia^2) + precip_residencia, data = sun)
w3_wea <- lm(log(flujo) ~ scale(pob_destino) + scale(pob_residencia) + scale(area_destino) + scale(area_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig + temp_residencia + I(temp_residencia^2) + precip_residencia, data = wed)
all_formula <- as.formula(paste0("log(flujo) ~ scale(pob_destino) + scale(pob_residencia) + scale(area_destino) + scale(area_residencia) + log(dist) + I(log(dist)^2) + contig + temp_residencia + I(temp_residencia^2) + precip_residencia + ", paste0("scale(",names(sun)[12:23],")", collapse = " + ")))

s4_all <- lm(formula = all_formula, data = sun)
w4_all <- lm(formula = all_formula, data = wed)

Comparison of Complex Models to Best Basic Model

Part 3: Visualizing Differences in Predictions of Mobility for Out-of-Sample Dates

Last two Sundays and Wednesdays in October were omitted from sample. Predictions for those days, below.

Simple Plots

sun_pred <- read_rds("~/GoogleDrive/PhD/Paper Three/mob_all.rds") %>% filter(codigo_destino != codigo_residencia & dia == "Sunday") %>% filter(data >= as.Date("2021-10-20")) %>% mutate(flujo_basic = exp(predict(s_basic, .)), flujo_complex = exp(predict(s_complex, .)))
wed_pred <- read_rds("~/GoogleDrive/PhD/Paper Three/mob_all.rds") %>% filter(codigo_destino != codigo_residencia & dia == "Wednesday") %>% filter(data >= as.Date("2021-10-20")) %>% mutate(flujo_basic = exp(predict(w_basic, .)), flujo_complex = exp(predict(w_complex, .)))

Both models underestimate mobility, but the complex model gets closer.

p1 <- bind_rows(sun_pred,wed_pred,.id = "Day") %>% mutate(Day = ifelse(Day=="1","Sundays","Wednesdays")) %>% ggplot(aes(flujo,flujo_basic,color=Day)) + geom_point(alpha = .35) + geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, alpha = .25) + theme_minimal() + labs(x = "Observed Flows", y = "Basic Model Predictions") + theme(legend.position = "none") 
p2 <- bind_rows(sun_pred,wed_pred,.id = "Day") %>% mutate(Day = ifelse(Day=="1","Sundays","Wednesdays")) %>% ggplot(aes(flujo,flujo_complex,color=Day)) + geom_point(alpha = .35) + geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, alpha = .25) + theme_minimal() + labs(x = "Observed Flows", y = "Complex Model Predictions") + theme(legend.position = "none") 
ggarrange(p1,p2)

bind_rows(sun_pred,wed_pred,.id = "Day") %>% mutate(Day = ifelse(Day=="1","Sundays","Wednesdays")) %>% ggplot(aes(flujo_basic,flujo_complex,color=Day)) + geom_point(alpha = .35) + geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, alpha = .25) + theme_minimal() + labs(x = "Basic Model Predictions", y = "Complex Model Predictions")

sun_res <- sun_pred %>% select(lon_residencia, lon_destino, lat_residencia, lat_destino, flujo, flujo_basic, flujo_complex) %>% bind_rows(setNames(.,c("lon_destino","lon_residencia","lat_destino","lat_residencia","flujo","flujo_basic","flujo_complex"))) %>% group_by(lon_residencia, lon_destino, lat_residencia, lat_destino) %>% summarise_all(sum) %>% ungroup() %>% mutate(id = row_number(), lon = lon_residencia, lat = lat_residencia) %>% select(id,lat,lon,flujo,flujo_basic,flujo_complex)

sun_des <- sun_pred %>% select(lon_residencia, lon_destino, lat_residencia, lat_destino, flujo, flujo_basic, flujo_complex) %>% bind_rows(setNames(.,c("lon_destino","lon_residencia","lat_destino","lat_residencia","flujo","flujo_basic","flujo_complex"))) %>% group_by(lon_residencia, lon_destino, lat_residencia, lat_destino) %>% summarise_all(sum) %>% ungroup() %>% mutate(id = row_number(), lon = lon_destino, lat = lat_destino) %>% select(id,lat,lon,flujo,flujo_basic,flujo_complex)

sun_geo <- bind_rows(sun_res,sun_des) %>% st_as_sf(coords = c("lon","lat"), crs = "+proj=longlat +datum=WGS84 +ellps=WGS84") %>% group_by(id) %>% summarise_if(is.numeric, mean, na.rm = TRUE) %>% st_cast("LINESTRING") %>% mutate_if(is.numeric,log) %>% arrange(flujo)

p1 <- ggplot() + geom_sf(data = map, color = "#404040", fill = "#101010") + geom_sf(data = sun_geo, aes(color = flujo)) + scale_colour_gradient2(low = "#191970", mid = "#00008B", high = "#ffff00", midpoint = 4.5) + theme_void() + theme(plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#101010"), legend.position = "none", plot.title = element_text(colour = "white", hjust = 0.5)) + labs(title = "Observed")

p2 <- ggplot() + geom_sf(data = map, color = "#404040", fill = "#101010") + geom_sf(data = arrange(sun_geo,flujo_basic), aes(color = flujo_basic)) + scale_colour_gradient2(low = "#191970", mid = "#00008B", high = "#ffff00", midpoint = 4.5) + theme_void() + theme(plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#101010"), legend.position = "none", plot.title = element_text(colour = "white", hjust = 0.5)) + labs(title = "Basic Gravity Model")

p3 <- ggplot() + geom_sf(data = map, color = "#404040", fill = "#101010") + geom_sf(data = arrange(sun_geo,flujo_complex), aes(color = flujo_complex)) + scale_colour_gradient2(low = "#191970", mid = "#00008B", high = "#ffff00", midpoint = 4.5) + theme_void() + theme(plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#101010"), legend.position = "none", plot.title = element_text(colour = "white", hjust = 0.5)) + labs(title = "Land Cover Data Model")

wed_res <- wed_pred %>% select(lon_residencia, lon_destino, lat_residencia, lat_destino, flujo, flujo_basic, flujo_complex) %>% bind_rows(setNames(.,c("lon_destino","lon_residencia","lat_destino","lat_residencia","flujo","flujo_basic","flujo_complex"))) %>% group_by(lon_residencia, lon_destino, lat_residencia, lat_destino)%>% summarise_all(sum) %>% ungroup() %>% mutate(id = row_number(), lon = lon_residencia, lat = lat_residencia) %>% select(id,lat,lon,flujo,flujo_basic,flujo_complex)

wed_des <- wed_pred %>% select(lon_residencia, lon_destino, lat_residencia, lat_destino, flujo, flujo_basic, flujo_complex) %>% bind_rows(setNames(.,c("lon_destino","lon_residencia","lat_destino","lat_residencia","flujo","flujo_basic","flujo_complex"))) %>% group_by(lon_residencia, lon_destino, lat_residencia, lat_destino)%>% summarise_all(sum) %>% ungroup() %>% mutate(id = row_number(), lon = lon_destino, lat = lat_destino) %>% select(id,lat,lon,flujo,flujo_basic,flujo_complex)

wed_geo <- bind_rows(wed_res,wed_des) %>% st_as_sf(coords = c("lon","lat"), crs = "+proj=longlat +datum=WGS84 +ellps=WGS84") %>% group_by(id) %>% summarise_if(is.numeric, mean, na.rm = TRUE) %>% st_cast("LINESTRING") %>% mutate_if(is.numeric,log) %>% arrange(flujo)

p4 <- ggplot() + geom_sf(data = map, color = "#404040", fill = "#101010") + geom_sf(data = wed_geo, aes(color = flujo)) + scale_colour_gradient2(low = "#191970", mid = "#00008B", high = "#ffff00", midpoint = 4.5) + theme_void() + theme(plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#101010"), legend.position = "none", plot.title = element_text(colour = "white", hjust = 0.5)) + labs(title = "Observed")

p5 <- ggplot() + geom_sf(data = map, color = "#404040", fill = "#101010") + geom_sf(data = arrange(wed_geo,flujo_basic), aes(color = flujo_basic)) + scale_colour_gradient2(low = "#191970", mid = "#00008B", high = "#ffff00", midpoint = 4.5) + theme_void() + theme(plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#101010"), legend.position = "none", plot.title = element_text(colour = "white", hjust = 0.5)) + labs(title = "Basic Gravity Model")

p6 <- ggplot() + geom_sf(data = map, color = "#404040", fill = "#101010") + geom_sf(data = arrange(wed_geo,flujo_complex), aes(color = flujo_complex)) + scale_colour_gradient2(low = "#191970", mid = "#00008B", high = "#ffff00", midpoint = 4.5) + theme_void() + theme(plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#101010"), legend.position = "none", plot.title = element_text(colour = "white", hjust = 0.5)) + labs(title = "Land Cover Data Model")
